In the past and still today, Chinese modernization is not a vision that China wants to impose on other countries, unlike Westernization which attempts to impose its views on the world at all costs. The era of socialism with Chinese characteristics is meant to provide a more comprehensive institutional guarantee, a more solid material basis and a more proactive spiritual force for national modernization. There is no single modernization model in the world. The basic essence of Chinese modernization is to bring satisfaction for the Chinese people and rejuvenation of the nation. In this episode of Bizbeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu explains.